OL,3,CO'Neill at centre of police probe into
OL,4,Calleged misconduct in public office
OL,6,FMr Robinson said that having free
OL,7,Fspeech and democracy would "sometimes
OL,8,Flead to robust exchanges".
OL,10,FHe said the idea that asking someone
OL,11,Fto breathe would "lead to the
OL,12,Fpolitical suffocation of an elected
OL,13,Frepresentative for two days" was
OL,14,F"intolerable".
OL,16,F"It cannot stand, it should not stand,
OL,17,Fand Democratic Unionists today will
OL,18,Fnot support the motion before the
OL,19,FAssembly," he said.
